<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900803-0009</DOCNO><DOCID>900803-0009.</DOCID><HL>   Kansas Gas andamp; Electric   Urges Rejection of Bid   By Kansas City Pandamp;L</HL><DATE>08/03/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C8</SO><CO>   KLT KGE</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><LP>   WICHITA, Kan. -- Kansas Gas andamp; Electric Co. said its boardrecommended that shareholders reject the $27-a-share, orabout $857 million, hostile tender offer launched last monthby Kansas City Power andamp; Light Inc.   The utility's response wasn't unexpected; earlier thisweek, it filed suit to, among other things, block itsunwanted suitor from looking at its holder list.</LP><TEXT>   Kansas Gas andamp; Electric said its financial adviser, MorganStanley andamp; Co., considered the offer price inadequate.Directors cited reservations about the &quot;many conditions&quot;Kansas City Pandamp;L placed on its offer, and the &quot;many months,perhaps more than a year, that could be required inattempting to satisfy those conditions, if indeed they canall be satisfied.&quot;   Kansas Gas andamp; Electric said the offer &quot;doesn't reflect thevalues inherent in the company,&quot; and &quot;raises substantial andserious legal questions and numerous uncertainties underfederal and state statutes.&quot; Kansas City Pandamp;L has said its bidis in &quot;full compliance with all applicable laws.&quot;   The two neighboring utilities already jointly own 94% of abig nuclear plant. Kansas City Pandamp;L launched its unusualhostile bid after repeated overtures for a friendly dealfailed.   Kansas City Pandamp;L said yesterday it believes the bid priceis &quot;full and fair.&quot; It added, &quot;We continue to emphasize ourstrong desire to achieve a negotiated transaction.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>